00:25:57,900 --> 00:26:00,834
I guess nobody could.

526
00:26:00,900 --> 00:26:03,767
He's all torn up. he doesn't
want anyone else to get hurt

527
00:26:03,834 --> 00:26:06,633
So he's doing what men
do best... avoiding it.

528
00:26:06,700 --> 00:26:09,200
So he hasn't found her? or
even started looking for her?

529
00:26:09,266 --> 00:26:10,200
Nope.

530
00:26:10,266 --> 00:26:11,567
Well, at least that buys me some time.

531
00:26:11,633 --> 00:26:14,567
Although his fiancee could
still show up at any minute.

532
00:26:14,633 --> 00:26:18,233
Hey, by then Sam will have
remembered that he's Jim.

533
00:26:18,300 --> 00:26:22,066
And you will live
happily ever after. right?

534
00:26:22,133 --> 00:26:25,867
Hey. hand me that box. I'll
take it out to the recycling bin.

535
00:26:25,934 --> 00:26:30,300
I can see now... how I
left my boys, my family.

536
00:26:30,366 --> 00:26:34,834
But I can't remember why. what happened?

537
00:26:34,900 --> 00:26:38,467
You're the only one who
knows. try and think back.

538
00:26:38,533 --> 00:26:40,767
You left Thomas, and
then you left Roger, too.

539
00:26:40,834 --> 00:26:43,166
I know you say that, but
that couldn't have happened.

540
00:26:43,233 --> 00:26:45,500
I'd never leave Roger.

541
00:26:45,567 --> 00:26:48,366
Please. why can't I remember?

542
00:26:49,934 --> 00:26:53,834
What happened? did
someone do that to you?

543
00:27:03,500 --> 00:27:05,300
Sweetheart, you poor thing.

544
00:27:05,366 --> 00:27:09,133
It's ok. I'm here now.

545
00:27:13,433 --> 00:27:16,033
I don't know how that happened.

546
00:27:16,099 --> 00:27:18,133
Was it Thomas?

547
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:21,366
Cause Roger said that he
didn't treat you very well.

548
00:27:21,433 --> 00:27:25,200
Or was it Roger? or someone else?

549
00:27:25,266 --> 00:27:28,966
No. Roger would never hurt
me. he always took care of me.

550
00:27:29,033 --> 00:27:32,033
Ok. well, either way, it's
something Roger knows about you.

551
00:27:32,099 --> 00:27:33,633
Maybe he talked to Elizabeth.

552
00:27:33,700 --> 00:27:35,200
His new wife?

553
00:27:35,266 --> 00:27:40,467
Well, she had to have asked
about you, about what happened.

554
00:27:40,533 --> 00:27:42,567
You've been hanging
around the old house.

555
00:27:42,633 --> 00:27:45,033
Is Elizabeth home right now?

556
00:27:45,099 --> 00:27:47,900
No. she went out.

557
00:27:47,966 --> 00:27:49,900
She's at the farmer's market.

558
00:27:58,834 --> 00:28:02,133
Hi, I was at your house the other day.

559
00:28:03,066 --> 00:28:04,900
Melinda, right?

560
00:28:04,966 --> 00:28:08,433
Sorry to bother you. I know
this is a difficult time.

561
00:28:08,500 --> 00:28:10,500
I'm sorry? what do you mean?

562
00:28:10,567 --> 00:28:13,999
Well, Roger must be upset
about his first wife.

563
00:28:14,066 --> 00:28:15,300
What are you talking about?

564
00:28:15,366 --> 00:28:18,600
Tammy's dead.

565
00:28:18,667 --> 00:28:21,266
They found her body yesterday.

566
00:28:23,600 --> 00:28:26,733
How did... how did... what happened?

567
00:28:26,800 --> 00:28:28,966
They're calling it a suicide.

568
00:28:29,033 --> 00:28:31,400
But she had bruises on her wrists.

569
00:28:33,333 --> 00:28:35,166
I think she was abused.

570
00:28:36,366 --> 00:28:37,867
Did she tell you that?

571
00:28:37,934 --> 00:28:41,533
No, she just looked really scared.

572
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:44,066
Like you do right now.

573
00:28:49,166 --> 00:28:52,733
I'm going to tell you the
same thing that I told her.

574
00:28:52,800 --> 00:28:54,266
You're not alone.

575
00:28:54,333 --> 00:28:57,834
There are people that can help.

576
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:00,700
I can help.

577
00:29:00,767 --> 00:29:03,099
It's safe to talk to me.

578
00:29:07,166 --> 00:29:10,633
I'm sorry. I have to get
home. I can't be late.

579
00:29:11,567 --> 00:29:15,300
Elizabeth!

580
00:29:20,467 --> 00:29:23,166
You're starting to remember, aren't you?

581
00:29:23,233 --> 00:29:26,300
I was just like her.

582
00:29:26,366 --> 00:29:28,633
I was so scared. I was
in such a dark place.

583
00:29:28,700 --> 00:29:31,366
You were abused, of course
you were in a dark place.

584
00:29:31,433 --> 00:29:34,800
No. no.

585
00:29:37,133 --> 00:29:41,233
I was in a really dark place.

586
00:29:56,099 --> 00:29:58,066
Tammy?

587
00:30:00,533 --> 00:30:03,966
I don't know how long I'd been in there.

588
00:30:04,033 --> 00:30:06,900
It seemed like forever.

589
00:30:06,966 --> 00:30:09,183
So, after you left your husband,

590
00:30:09,218 --> 00:30:11,400
Is that how Roger would punish you?

591
00:30:11,467 --> 00:30:13,500
No.

592
00:30:13,567 --> 00:30:17,767
That's where Roger kept
me after he kidnapped me.

593
00:30:29,830 --> 00:30:34,083
Thomas was working late,
I was up doing the dishes.

594
00:30:35,277 --> 00:30:40,430
I thought Roger had gone
home. But suddenly he was...

595
00:30:40,931 --> 00:30:46,039
standing right behind me. He
said he knew that I wasn't happy.

596
00:30:46,833 --> 00:30:49,900
And that he could make me happy.

597
00:30:49,967 --> 00:30:52,000
Was there something
going on between you two?

598
00:30:52,067 --> 00:30:54,167
No! I barely knew him.

599
00:30:54,233 --> 00:30:58,100
He was... he was just some
guy doing work on our house.

600
00:30:58,167 --> 00:31:01,267
But the neighbors told your
husband they suspected something.

601
00:31:01,334 --> 00:31:02,766
I remember seeing him talking to them.

602
00:31:02,833 --> 00:31:07,434
I just... i just thought he was
just trying to round up more work.

603
00:31:07,499 --> 00:31:11,766
So he wanted them to suspect
something to cover his tracks.

604
00:31:11,833 --> 00:31:14,334
What happened after he locked you up?

605
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:17,200
I lost count of the days.

606
00:31:19,000 --> 00:31:22,100
I thought I was losing my mind.

607
00:31:22,167 --> 00:31:26,233
I remember hearing my boys' voices.

608
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:29,866
I couldn't tell what was real anymore.

609
00:31:29,933 --> 00:31:35,466
Then one day, it all just changed.

610
00:31:36,367 --> 00:31:38,566
Upsy-daisey. there we go.

611
00:31:38,633 --> 00:31:43,033
Ooh, these are a little tight, huh?

612
00:31:45,866 --> 00:31:50,833
Suddenly he was so kind and caring.

613
00:31:55,866 --> 00:31:57,133
It's ok.

614
00:31:57,200 --> 00:31:59,167
At first it was just food.

615
00:31:59,233 --> 00:32:01,100
And then it was bigger things.

616
00:32:01,167 --> 00:32:04,434
Like letting me go outside.

617
00:32:04,499 --> 00:32:08,533
Eventually he let me take
trips to the market alone.

618
00:32:10,666 --> 00:32:12,833
So you started to trust him.

619
00:32:12,900 --> 00:32:14,599
Oh God, how could I have?!

620
00:32:14,666 --> 00:32:16,434
You were brainwashed.

621
00:32:16,499 --> 00:32:18,033
It happens. I don't know why.

622
00:32:18,100 --> 00:32:23,434
It's called stockholm syndrome.

623
00:32:23,499 --> 00:32:25,434
Did you ever try to get away?

624
00:32:25,499 --> 00:32:27,700
No. no!

625
00:32:27,766 --> 00:32:29,267
I couldn't.

626
00:32:29,334 --> 00:32:33,466
He threatened that if I did, he
would kill my family, my boys.

627
00:32:33,533 --> 00:32:35,733
So the only escape was to kill yourself.

628
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:37,800
No, I wouldn't.

629
00:32:37,866 --> 00:32:40,533
Then what happened that day?

630
00:32:40,599 --> 00:32:43,633
I was at the market.

631
00:32:43,700 --> 00:32:47,434
For some reason I was late getting home.

632
00:32:47,499 --> 00:32:49,400
Hey, honey.

633
00:32:49,466 --> 00:32:51,967
I was worried about you.

634
00:32:52,033 --> 00:32:55,200
Sorry, I'm fine.

635
00:32:55,267 --> 00:32:58,499
No, you're not fine.

636
00:32:58,566 --> 00:32:59,766
What's going on, darling?

637
00:32:59,833 --> 00:33:04,167
Nothing, it's... nothing.

638
00:33:05,967 --> 00:33:10,766
You know you can't lie to me.

639
00:33:10,833 --> 00:33:13,416
Did something happen in town

640
00:33:13,451 --> 00:33:16,000
you want to tell me about? Hmm?

641
00:33:16,067 --> 00:33:20,933
No, I must've lost track of time.

642
00:33:22,133 --> 00:33:24,100
After that he told me to
go upstairs and rest...

643
00:33:24,167 --> 00:33:27,566
That he would make me something to eat.

644
00:33:27,633 --> 00:33:28,866
We ate.

645
00:33:28,933 --> 00:33:33,000
Then, I felt sleepy.

646
00:33:42,466 --> 00:33:45,100
And I wanted to say something, but...

647
00:33:45,167 --> 00:33:49,067
But the words wouldn't come out.

648
00:33:49,133 --> 00:33:51,733
Roger always told me,

649
00:33:51,800 --> 00:33:53,967
"I decide when you leave. "

650
00:33:56,200 --> 00:33:59,967
I guess he decided it was time.

651
00:34:02,466 --> 00:34:04,367
After he kidnapped and stockholmed her?

652
00:34:04,434 --> 00:34:05,981
That's possible. Right?

653
00:34:06,016 --> 00:34:07,599
I mean, I'm not making this stuff up?

654
00:34:07,666 --> 00:34:10,133
No, what you're describing
is exactly how it works.

655
00:34:10,200 --> 00:34:12,067
He grabs her. He locks her up.

656
00:34:12,133 --> 00:34:14,233
He threatens to kill
her family if she runs.

657
00:34:14,300 --> 00:34:16,000
She's scared out of her wits.

658
00:34:16,067 --> 00:34:19,100
So what if he's doing the
same thing to Elizabeth?

659
00:34:19,167 --> 00:34:20,933
You said Elizabeth seemed
scared, which is good,

660
00:34:21,000 --> 00:34:22,599
That tells me she isn't
completely brainwashed.

661
00:34:22,666 --> 00:34:24,367
Look, I want you to call
Det. Blair and find out

662
00:34:24,434 --> 00:34:26,100
if anyone matching
Elizabeth's description

663
00:34:26,167 --> 00:34:27,900
has gone up missing in the last year.

664
00:34:27,967 --> 00:34:29,181
If she has a family anywhere,

665
00:34:29,216 --> 00:34:30,466
we need to get them somewhere safe.

666
00:34:30,533 --> 00:34:31,967
And what're you gonna do?

667
00:34:32,033 --> 00:34:34,566
Just call me when it's done.

668
00:34:47,466 --> 00:34:49,434
Elizabeth, are you here?

669
00:34:57,300 --> 00:34:59,499
Roger spied on me sometimes.

670
00:34:59,566 --> 00:35:01,233
I never knew when it would be.

671
00:35:01,300 --> 00:35:03,683
So you're saying he could've seen me

672
00:35:03,718 --> 00:35:06,067
talking to Elizabeth at the market.

673
00:35:25,833 --> 00:35:26,600
Is someone there?

674
00:35:29,900 --> 00:35:30,500
Help.

675
00:35:33,900 --> 00:35:34,600
Help.

676
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:56,200
Oh, my God.

677
00:35:56,300 --> 00:35:58,167
Are you ok?

678
00:36:01,933 --> 00:36:03,933
I'm so sorry.

679
00:36:24,399 --> 00:36:26,200
Stay away from her!

680
00:36:26,267 --> 00:36:28,334
Don't do this! I love you.

681
00:36:28,399 --> 00:36:30,600
Is that what you said to Tammy? is it?

682
00:36:30,666 --> 00:36:32,033
Before you killed her?!

683
00:36:32,100 --> 00:36:33,867
She told you that?! she's insane!

684
00:36:33,933 --> 00:36:35,867
She says she sees ghosts!

685
00:36:35,933 --> 00:36:40,766
Well, maybe she'll see yours soon!

686
00:36:40,833 --> 00:36:41,867
That's enough!

687
00:36:41,933 --> 00:36:43,033
Get out of the way!

688
00:36:43,100 --> 00:36:44,933
Put it down, the police
are on their way. Ok?

689
00:36:45,000 --> 00:36:46,967
He's gonna get his
punishment. Put it down.

690
00:36:47,033 --> 00:36:50,200
Punishment for what? having a wife?

691
00:36:50,267 --> 00:36:53,399
Who is gonna believe
that I was held captive?

692
00:36:53,466 --> 00:36:56,000
They'll say I could've
run. He'll get away with it.

693
00:36:56,067 --> 00:36:57,867
He thinks of everything.

694
00:36:57,933 --> 00:37:00,167
Then you have to think of
everything... your family.

695
00:37:00,234 --> 00:37:03,633
All right, if you kill him,
you're gonna get put away.

696
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:06,533
And you'll be kept
away from them forever.

697
00:37:06,600 --> 00:37:10,100
Think of your family. Put it down.

698
00:37:14,399 --> 00:37:17,433
Now you'll know what it
feels like to be a prisoner.

699
00:37:22,833 --> 00:37:26,416
No, no, please. Don't leave.

700
00:37:26,451 --> 00:37:30,000
Help me! Please! Elizabeth!

701
00:37:40,766 --> 00:37:43,167
At least one of us got to go home.

702
00:37:46,766 --> 00:37:48,399
Thank you.

703
00:37:49,933 --> 00:37:51,500
I can help you talk to your family.

704
00:37:51,535 --> 00:37:53,067
You could say goodbye.

705
00:37:53,133 --> 00:37:55,683
No, they think I abandoned them.

706
00:37:55,718 --> 00:37:58,234
And I almost did.

707
00:37:58,300 --> 00:38:01,833
How could they ever forgive me?

708
00:38:01,900 --> 00:38:04,733
You didn't abandon them, not really.

709
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:08,700
There was always a piece
of you that remembered.

710
00:38:11,033 --> 00:38:14,733
I got your personal
effects from the station.

711
00:38:14,800 --> 00:38:18,533
I almost missed this, it
was folded so many times.

712
00:38:24,234 --> 00:38:26,800
That's my little boy.

713
00:38:26,867 --> 00:38:28,967
That's Rich.

714
00:38:32,766 --> 00:38:35,267
That's why I was late that night.

715
00:38:43,800 --> 00:38:47,533
I stared at that picture for hours.

716
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:51,433
My heart just aching.

717
00:38:51,499 --> 00:38:55,700
You must've put it in
your wallet that day.

718
00:38:55,766 --> 00:38:57,800
Roger knew that you
were covering something.

719
00:38:57,867 --> 00:38:59,633
He knew that he was losing control.

720
00:38:59,700 --> 00:39:01,967
And he just couldn't let that happen.

721
00:39:02,033 --> 00:39:04,133
Let's go home.

722
00:39:07,133 --> 00:39:09,334
Do me a favor, get
your brother a soda, ok?

723
00:39:09,399 --> 00:39:11,533
Thanks.

724
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:16,766
So you're saying you talked
with my wife's spirit.

725
00:39:17,867 --> 00:39:21,033
That's why you came to me first.

726
00:39:21,100 --> 00:39:22,399
That's, uh...

727
00:39:22,466 --> 00:39:25,234
Crazy. Yeah, I know.

728
00:39:25,300 --> 00:39:27,900
Um, Tammy...

729
00:39:27,967 --> 00:39:31,000
Sarah, she needed some
answers about things.

730
00:39:31,067 --> 00:39:34,100
She couldn't remember
what happened to her.

731
00:39:34,167 --> 00:39:35,466
And now she does.

732
00:39:35,533 --> 00:39:37,200
I'm so sorry, Thomas.

733
00:39:37,267 --> 00:39:40,967
I wanted to grow old with you, too.

734
00:39:42,167 --> 00:39:46,133
I wanted to see Joe hit
his first grand slam,

735
00:39:46,200 --> 00:39:47,967
And Rich get his braces off

736
00:39:48,033 --> 00:39:52,133
And I wanted to buy that
houseboat on the lake

737
00:39:52,200 --> 00:39:56,167
And fill it with grandkids
just like we talked about.

738
00:39:56,234 --> 00:39:58,900
She says there's so much that
she wanted to do with you,

739
00:39:58,967 --> 00:40:01,533
The houseboat on the lake.

740
00:40:01,600 --> 00:40:03,766
How did you know about that?

741
00:40:03,833 --> 00:40:05,399
We had this joke.

742
00:40:05,466 --> 00:40:09,133
We were gonna name
the boat, 2 old coots.

743
00:40:09,200 --> 00:40:11,499
2 old coots?

744
00:40:16,399 --> 00:40:20,633
She's really here, isn't she?

745
00:40:20,700 --> 00:40:23,566
Oh God, she must hate me.

746
00:40:23,633 --> 00:40:25,600
I just left her there!

747
00:40:25,666 --> 00:40:29,399
6 years and I never went after her.

748
00:40:29,466 --> 00:40:32,666
I should've looked harder for her.

749
00:40:32,733 --> 00:40:36,067
All she went through. I did nothing.

750
00:40:36,133 --> 00:40:39,499
How can I forgive myself?

751
00:40:39,566 --> 00:40:44,600
You have to. please tell him that.

752
00:40:44,666 --> 00:40:48,100
Roger kept me prisoner for so long.

753
00:40:48,167 --> 00:40:52,000
He used guilt, fear,
remorse to keep me tied up.

754
00:40:52,067 --> 00:40:54,766
Don't let him do that to you,

755
00:40:54,801 --> 00:40:57,466
don't give him that victory.

756
00:40:57,533 --> 00:40:59,600
I'm free now.

757
00:40:59,666 --> 00:41:02,600
I want you to be, too.

758
00:41:02,666 --> 00:41:04,833
She needs that to move on,

759
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:07,433
to know that you're free, like she is.

760
00:41:07,499 --> 00:41:12,267
I love you so much. You were our world.

761
00:41:12,334 --> 00:41:17,600
I know. I felt that.

762
00:41:17,666 --> 00:41:19,566
She knows that.

763
00:41:19,633 --> 00:41:21,915
And you did helped her

764
00:41:21,950 --> 00:41:24,267
even if you didn't know it.

765
00:41:24,334 --> 00:41:26,533
Hey, dad.

766
00:41:30,700 --> 00:41:32,598
Will you make sure

767
00:41:32,633 --> 00:41:34,566
that he tells them
everything that happened?

768
00:41:36,267 --> 00:41:39,733
That I always loved them?

769
00:41:42,800 --> 00:41:45,666
I see something.

770
00:41:45,733 --> 00:41:46,867
It's a light.

771
00:41:46,933 --> 00:41:48,800
That's for you.

772
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:06,334
Come here.

773
00:42:29,867 --> 00:42:30,833
Thanks.

774
00:42:30,900 --> 00:42:32,700
Anything good in there?

775
00:42:32,766 --> 00:42:34,733
Yeah. Huge story.

776
00:42:34,800 --> 00:42:36,348
Did you read about

777
00:42:36,383 --> 00:42:37,967
that guy who kidnapped those 2 women?

778
00:42:38,033 --> 00:42:40,133
Yeah. Crazy, huh?

779
00:42:40,200 --> 00:42:42,967
What a happy ending for the woman.

780
00:42:43,033 --> 00:42:44,766
Can you imagine what it was like

781
00:42:44,801 --> 00:42:46,499
for her to see her family again?

782
00:42:46,566 --> 00:42:49,100
Yeah. Thank God the
police got there in time.

783
00:42:50,566 --> 00:42:54,300
She gets a real second chance.

784
00:42:54,366 --> 00:42:56,300
Kinda like me.

785
00:43:01,967 --> 00:43:04,366
I just can't keep
carrying this thing around.

786
